JNC 08/OCt/25

More testing and debugging done on the J2000 coordinates. The code has two compile time options (a) to use SLA to do the coordinate transformation or (b) to use NOVAS. The SLA version matches the positions obtained from the 1s LTA file, and  as such seems fine. Still more testing is needed for the NOVAS issues. There may be finer issues related to use of UTC instead of UT1 in computing the hour angle. If so, this correction would also need to be made to gvfits. At the moment there is the option to read in the BulletinA corrections to get the UTC to UT1 conversion, but it is not used.

Also added the option of specifying an LTA time (in seconds) when converting all of the rawvisibility data to FITS (ALL_DATA option). This helps reduce the file size considerably. This is very useful when making a large scale image for finding background sources to check astrometry.

This version also includes reading in of the binary corr and scan headers. However currently the Das pipeline appears to be filling wrong/incomplete information in these headers, so until that is resolved, one needs to seprately provide all of the meta data in the svfits_par.txt file. 

Some details on the files in this commit are given below.

